criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  age of ≥ 18 years;

          -  indication for MT according to valid guidelines;

          -  modified Rankin score (mRS) of ≤ 2 before stroke onset;

          -  baseline Alberta Stroke Program Early CT Score (ASPECTS) of ≥ 6;

          -  MCA occlusion in M1 or M2 segment with or without intracranial ICA occlusion;

          -  estimated onset-to-skin cut time of ≤6 h or core/penumbra mismatch in cases with
             wake-up stroke or stroke with unknown onset;

          -  MT failure with TICI score of 0-1 declared by an interventional neuroradiologist and
             expectation to achieve recanalization within 24 h from stroke onset.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  indication for MT according to valid guidelines;

          -  thrombocyte count of ≤ 100,000/µL;

          -  contraindication for general anesthesia
